{"kind":"symbol","primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"nonisolated","kind":"attribute"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"tint","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"_","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"tint","kind":"internalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore5ColorV","text":"Color","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Color","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"?) -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"some","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP","text":"View","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"\n","kind":"text"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"parameters":[{"name":"tint","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The tint ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Color","type":"reference"},{"text":" to apply.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"kind":"parameters"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use this method to override the default accent color for this view."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Unlike an app’s accent color, which can be overridden by user"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"preference, the tint color is always respected and should be used as a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"way to provide additional meaning to the control."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This example shows Answer and Decline buttons with ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ShapeStyle\/green","isActive":true},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ShapeStyle\/red","isActive":true},{"text":" tint colors, respectively.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["struct ControlTint: View {","    var body: some View {","        HStack {","            Button {","                \/\/ Answer the call","            } label: {","                Label(\"Answer\", systemImage: \"phone\")","            }","            .tint(.green)","            Button {","                \/\/ Decline the call","            } label: {","                Label(\"Decline\", systemImage: \"phone.down\")","            }","            .tint(.red)","        }","        .buttonStyle(.borderedProminent)","        .padding()","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Some controls adapt to the tint color differently based on their style,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the current platform, and the surrounding context. For example, in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"macOS, a button with the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PrimitiveButtonStyle\/bordered"},{"type":"text","text":" style doesn’t"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"tint its background, but one with the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PrimitiveButtonStyle\/borderedProminent"},{"type":"text","text":" style does. In macOS, neither"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of these button styles tint their label, but they do in other platforms."}]}]}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/openswiftui\/viewthatfits\/tint(_:)"]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ViewThatFits\/tint(_:)"},"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI","doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\